The HD 145934 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 145934 is a star with 1.75 times the mass of the Sun, and 5.38 times its radius. It is located 743.25 light years away from the solar system.

HD 145934 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 145934 system


HD 145934 b

HD 145934 b was discovered by the W. M. Keck Observatory observatory, in 2015-02, using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 4.60 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 145934 b is 725.040 times the mass of Earth. The radius of HD 145934 b is 13.300 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 145934 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
